.TH ICAL\-GUY 1 "2026-02-15" "ical-guy 0.1.0" "General Commands Manual"
.SH NAME
ical\-guy \- query macOS calendar events and output as JSON
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ical\-guy
.RI [ subcommand ]
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ical\-guy
is a command\-line tool for querying macOS calendar events via EventKit and
outputting results as JSON.
It is designed as a modern replacement for icalBuddy.
.PP
When no subcommand is given,
.B events
is used by default.
.PP
JSON output is pretty\-printed with sorted keys when stdout is a terminal,
and compact when piped.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B events
Query calendar events and output as JSON.
This is the default subcommand.
.TP
.B calendars
List available calendars as JSON.
.TP
.B help
Show help information.
.SH EVENTS OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-from " date"
Start date for the query range.
Defaults to the start of today.
See
.B DATE FORMATS
below.
.TP
.BI \-\-to " date"
End date for the query range.
Defaults to the end of the start date.
See
.B DATE FORMATS
below.
.TP
.BI \-\-include\-calendars " calendars"
Only include events from these calendars.
Comma\-separated list of calendar titles.
.TP
.BI \-\-exclude\-calendars " calendars"
Exclude events from these calendars.
Comma\-separated list of calendar titles.
.TP
.B \-\-exclude\-all\-day
Exclude all\-day events from the output.
.TP
.BI \-\-limit " n"
Maximum number of events to return.
.SH DATE FORMATS
The
.B \-\-from
and
.B \-\-to
options accept the following date formats:
.TP
.B today
Start of today.
.TP
.B tomorrow
Start of tomorrow.
.TP
.B yesterday
Start of yesterday.
.TP
.BI today+ N
.I N
days from today (e.g.,
.BR today+7 ).
.TP
.BI today\- N
.I N
days before today (e.g.,
.BR today\-3 ).
.TP
.B now
Current date and time.
.TP
.I YYYY\-MM\-DD
ISO 8601 date (e.g.,
.BR 2026\-03\-15 ).
.SH OUTPUT
.SS Events
A JSON array of event objects.
Each object contains:
.TP
.B id
Unique event identifier.
.TP
.B title
Event title.
.TP
.B startDate
Event start as an ISO 8601 datetime string.
.TP
.B endDate
Event end as an ISO 8601 datetime string.
.TP
.B isAllDay
Boolean indicating whether the event is all\-day.
.TP
.B location
Event location, or null.
.TP
.B notes
Event notes, or null.
.TP
.B url
Event URL, or null.
.TP
.B calendar
Object with
.BR id ,
.BR title ,
.BR type ,
.BR source ,
and
.B color
fields.
.TP
.B attendees
Array of attendee name strings.
.TP
.B isRecurring
Boolean indicating whether the event is recurring.
.TP
.B status
Event status (e.g., "confirmed").
.SS Calendars
A JSON array of calendar objects.
Each object contains:
.TP
.B id
Unique calendar identifier.
.TP
.B title
Calendar name.
.TP
.B type
Calendar type (e.g., "calDAV", "subscription").
.TP
.B source
Calendar source (e.g., "iCloud").
.TP
.B color
Hex color code (e.g., "#306793").
.SH EXAMPLES
Show today's events:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ical\-guy
.fi
.RE
.PP
Show events for the next 7 days:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ical\-guy events \-\-from today \-\-to today+7
.fi
.RE
.PP
Show tomorrow's events from the Work calendar, excluding all\-day events:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ical\-guy events \-\-from tomorrow \-\-to tomorrow \\
    \-\-include\-calendars Work \-\-exclude\-all\-day
.fi
.RE
.PP
Show the next 5 events in the next 30 days:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ical\-guy events \-\-from today \-\-to today+30 \-\-limit 5
.fi
.RE
.PP
List available calendars:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ical\-guy calendars
.fi
.RE
.PP
Pipe events to
.BR jq (1)
to filter recurring events:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ical\-guy events | jq '[.[] | select(.isRecurring == true)]'
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B >0
An error occurred (e.g., calendar access denied).
.SH NOTES
On first run, macOS will prompt for calendar access permission.
The tool requires Full Disk Access or Calendar access to be granted in
System Settings > Privacy & Security > Calendars.
.PP
Requires macOS 14 (Sonoma) or later.
